# Mee'ma - Behind the scenes[]

Mee'ma appeared in "The Spy Dancer," a non-canon short film released as part of the second volume of the Star Wars: Visions series, directed by Julien Chheng and written by Chheng and Daniel Clarke. The animated short, produced by Studio La Cachette, was released on Disney+ on May 4, 2023.  Mee'ma was voiced by Barbara Weber-Scaff, who also provided additional voices for the short. While not stated in the short, Mee'ma's name was provided in the episode's credits. Concept art was created for Mee'ma performing in the metal arch and in a lineup featuring other characters from the short.

The score for "The Spy Dancer" was completed before the final animation. This allowed for actions and moments in the short—including Mee'ma's movements—to be animated to specific musical queues and motifs.
metadata.title: Mee'ma

# Sandro Alimander - Behind the scenes[]

Sandro Alimander appeared in Star Wars: Galactic Starcruiser, an immersive hotel and entertainment experience which launched in March 2022 at the Walt Disney World Resort. In audition sides posted for the character by The Walt Disney Company, the musician composes an impromptu love song for the superstar with the help of the Halcyon's guests. Alimander appeared as either a Togruta or as a Mirialan, though in certain occasions, this character was portrayed as a human.
metadata.title: Sandro Alimander

# Galactic Dreamer - Behind the scenes[]

"Galactic Dreamer" is also the title of the same song out-of-universe. The song was composed by Yoshiaki Dewa and sung by Nonpe, and released for digital streaming on October 15, 2021 as part of Star Wars: Visions – Tatooine Rhapsody (Original Soundtrack). The soundtrack also includes an instrumental version of the song. The soundtrack contains the song sung in Japanese, but not sung in English as in the English dub of "Tatooine Rhapsody." The creators of "Tatooine Rhapsody" told interviewers they wanted to create the episode as a rock and roll space opera.

# Lothalite children's rhyme - Behind the scenes[]

The Lothalite children's rhyme first appeared in "Path of the Jedi," the tenth episode of the first season of the animated television series Star Wars Rebels which aired on January 5, 2015.
metadata.title: Lothalite children's rhyme

metadata.content:
# Lothalite children's rhyme

Lothalite children's rhyme


Attribution information

Performer(s)
Ezra Bridger



Publication information

Type
Rhyme



General information

Genre
For children


[Source]

On the Outer Rim planet Lothal, the native Loth-wolves were featured in a popular rhyme for Lothalite children, alongside Loth-rats and Loth-cats. The rhyme was recited as "Loth-rat, Loth-cat, Loth-wolf, run. Pick a path and all is done," and was used as a method of selection. As a child, Lothalite Ezra Bridger was taught the rhyme by his mother prior to her imprisonment by the Galactic Empire in 12 BBY. Bridger recited the rhyme in two instances: to select one of three paths in the Lothal Jedi Temple when he was brought there by his Master Kanan Jarrus in 4 BBY, and again to decide which direction to go while on Lothal in 1 BBY. The Galactic Society of Creature Enthusiasts' Director of Creature Cartography Ardis San Tekka mentioned the rhyme in the Loth-wolf entry of her bestiary at some point after the Battle of Exegol in 35 ABY.
metadata.title: Lothalite children's rhyme
